# REASONING_LINK_DESIGN.md sec 16.16.8's registered sha256 reuse gate for
# Phase-2b's 6 reused OFF-arm cells (2 corpora x 3 seeds x 5 trajectory
# checkpoints = 30 .pt files). Pinned ONCE, this design session
# (2026-07-10), against the ORIGINAL box archive --
# youthful-indigo-turkey:/home/nvidia/chapter2/deltanet_rd/results/phase2/
# ckpts/ -- via `ssh youthful-indigo-turkey "cd .../ckpts && sha256sum
# *.pt"`. Never regenerated from a local/SSD copy (that would make the
# check tautological). Verified directly at pin time: exactly 30 files
# present on box, matching this design's own expectation exactly (6 cells
# x 5 checkpoints, zero missing/extra). Format: standard sha256sum output
# (digest, two spaces, basename) so `sha256sum -c` / `diff <(sha256sum
# ...) <(sort this file)` both work directly against it. Mirrors the
# K=69 precedent exactly: experiment-runs/2026-07-07_keyanchor_scaling_wide/
# gates/keyanchor_scaling_wide_k69_copy_manifest.sha256.
#
# Consulted by (registered build task, sec 16.16.9, not yet built): a
# Python-level gate function analogous to phase2_gate_enforce.py's own
# read-only verdict pattern, called before Phase-2b's new eval-L_query
# pass (sec 16.16.3) reads any of these 6 reused cells' checkpoints, plus
# a standalone bash-level `sha256sum -c` check in whatever chain script
# orchestrates the 12-cell launch (mirrors keyanchor_scaling_wide_chain.sh's
# own belt-and-suspenders GATE (c) structure).
